<article about="/us/blog/threat-insight/baza-valentines-day" class="node--type--blog-post node--view-mode--full node node-blog-full _legacy_content _blog-full">
  



  <div class="breadcrumbs _legacy_element _breadcrumbs"><div class="nav-crumbs"><div class="breadcrumb__item"><a href="/us/blog" class="breadcrum__item-link">Blog</a></div><div class="breadcrumb__item"><a href="/us/blog/threat-insight" class="breadcrum__item-link">Threat Insight</a></div><div class="breadcrumb__item">
            A Baza Valentines Day          </div></div></div>

  <div class="blog-banner">
    <div class="blog-banner__image">      <picture>
                  <source srcset="/sites/default/files/styles/image_1920_750/public/misc/BLOG_Valentines.jpg.webp?itok=aCsX_1vv 1x" media="screen and (min-width: 1440px)" type="image/webp" width="1920" height="750"/>
              <source srcset="/sites/default/files/styles/image_1024_400/public/misc/BLOG_Valentines.jpg.webp?itok=4B3ibSqC 1x" media="screen and (min-width: 1024px)" type="image/webp" width="1024" height="400"/>
              <source srcset="/sites/default/files/styles/image_768_375/public/misc/BLOG_Valentines.jpg.webp?itok=SxYyVAc0 1x" media="screen and (min-width: 768px)" type="image/webp" width="768" height="375"/>
              <source srcset="/sites/default/files/styles/image_1920_750/public/misc/BLOG_Valentines.jpg.webp?itok=aCsX_1vv 1x" media="screen and (min-width: 1440px)" type="image/webp" width="1920" height="750"/>
              <source srcset="/sites/default/files/styles/image_1024_400/public/misc/BLOG_Valentines.jpg.webp?itok=4B3ibSqC 1x" media="screen and (min-width: 1024px)" type="image/webp" width="1024" height="400"/>
              <source srcset="/sites/default/files/styles/image_768_375/public/misc/BLOG_Valentines.jpg.webp?itok=SxYyVAc0 1x" media="screen and (min-width: 768px)" type="image/webp" width="768" height="375"/>
                  <img loading="lazy" src="/sites/default/files/styles/image_768_300/public/misc/BLOG_Valentines.jpg.webp?itok=uja4Bo1l" width="768" height="300" alt="Bazar Valentines" typeof="foaf:Image" />

  </picture>

    <div class="blog-banner__gradient-overlay"></div>
    <div class="blog-banner__heading-wrap">
      
      


<h1 class="blog-banner__heading">
      <span>A Baza Valentines Day</span>

  </h1>

    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="blog-content">
    <div class="blog-content__sharethis sharethis_toolbox sharethis_32x32_style">
      <div class="blog-content__sharethis_label sharethis__label">Share with your network!</div>
      <div class="blog-content__sharethis_buttons sharethis_buttons">
        <div class="sharethis-inline-share-buttons"></div>
        
<span class="addthis_button_subscribe at300b UNCONVERTED" title=Subscribe>
  <span class="at-icon-wrapper block-subscribe-button__trigger block-subscribe-button__addthis"></span>
</span>


      </div>
    </div>
        <div class="blog-content__metadata blog-content__metadata-author">
      <span class="blog-content__date">  <time datetime="2021-02-11T16:28:07Z">February 11, 2021</time>

</span>
        <span class="blog-content__author">
                Proofpoint Threat Research Team
  
        </span>
    </div>
    <div class="node-full__body blog-content__body">  <p paraeid="{fbb229e2-ad19-4d39-b73f-89e5de916d3f}{159}" paraid="811555148"><meta charset="utf-8"></p>

<p>In 2020, Proofpoint observed an increase in BazaLoader campaign volume peaking in October. During that time, we observed specific campaigns correlated to public reports of affiliate campaigns delivering BazaLoader and associated with <a href="https://www.fireeye.com/blog/threat-research/2020/10/kegtap-and-singlemalt-with-a-ransomware-chaser.html" target="_blank">Ryuk ransomware infections</a>. Notably, in January 2021, Proofpoint researchers observed a few of BazaLoader campaigns leveraging Valentine's Day themes such as flowers and lingerie. The attack chains required an unusual amount of human interaction before a payload was delivered. While we track a fair amount of BazaLoader delivered by TA800 and TA572, these campaigns are not associated with either TA800 or TA572 and are likely leveraged by other affiliates.&nbsp;</p>

<h3>BazaLoader Origin&nbsp;</h3>

<p>BazaLoader is a downloader written in C++ whose primary function is to download and execute additional modules. It was first observed in the wild in April 2020 and since has steadily been adopted by more actors. Proofpoint has observed at least six variants of Bazaloader signaling active and continued development. One of the earliest BazaLoader variants Proofpoint researchers identified used ".bazar" top-level domains for command-and-control communication. The ".bazar" TLDs are associated with cryptocurrency DNS named Emercoin using Blockchain services reported in early April 2020. Today, we do not see the same association to cryptocurrency infrastructure, but it is relevant to its provenance.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<h3>Valentines Day&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3>

<p>Proofpoint researchers have spotted multiple BazaLoader campaigns in January and February 2021 involving the tactic of heavily relying on human interaction with different sites, PDF attachments, and <a href="https://www.proofpoint.com/us/corporate-blog/post/top-5-email-phishing-lures">email lures</a>. There were a range of lure and subject topics, including compact storage devices, office supplies, pharmaceutical supplies, and sports nutrition, but what stuck out were campaigns that were timely and relevant to the upcoming Valentines Day holiday. The campaigns were spread across a diverse set of companies and sectors.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>

<p>Valentines Day, while not abused to the level of other holidays, presents an opportunity for a variety of actors. The FBI Boston field office has posted public warnings of romance scams. While this is not a romance scam, it is&nbsp;<a href="https://www.fbi.gov/contact-us/field-offices/boston/news/press-releases/fbi-cautions-public-to-beware-of-romance-scammers-looking-for-more-than-love" target="_blank">an example of social engineering</a>&nbsp;well-timed with the Valentines Day holiday.</p>

<h3 paraeid="{61a8eee6-9be4-4dab-bae9-1867380ad4ed}{222}" paraid="1720500835">Infection Chain&nbsp;</h3>

<p paraeid="{61a8eee6-9be4-4dab-bae9-1867380ad4ed}{228}" paraid="17039650"><img src="data:image/png;base64," unselectable="on">&nbsp;<em>Figure 1:&nbsp;Infection Chain&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{afbd0fae-b40e-44ab-9eb3-11421c83dd0c}{232}" paraid="2123192335">The infection chain is consistent in the latest campaigns.&nbsp;The websites the user would browse to are fake, but the actors took care to have the physical addresses in the below images match&nbsp;a&nbsp;near-legitimate location.&nbsp;For example,&nbsp;Ajour&nbsp;Lingerie&nbsp;is not located at&nbsp;1133 50th St, Brooklyn, NY&nbsp;11219, but this address is in physical proximity to a&nbsp;legitimate&nbsp;website and physical business&nbsp;called&nbsp;the Lingerie Shop.&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{e7e93988-065a-4e99-adfc-b4b3ecc253df}{23}" paraid="1093828874"><img src="data:image/png;base64," unselectable="on">&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{db940a08-45ea-45e9-8dd1-00564dff8e39}{24}" paraid="1314628942"><em>Figure&nbsp;2:&nbsp;physical&nbsp;address&nbsp;to digital&nbsp;website&nbsp;</em></p>

<h3 paraeid="{7e8b84b9-8e35-413c-bf23-fd06962f92eb}{114}" paraid="1036118687">Lingerie&nbsp;at&nbsp;Ajour&nbsp;</h3>

<p paraeid="{7e8b84b9-8e35-413c-bf23-fd06962f92eb}{122}" paraid="1814464805">This campaign delivered&nbsp;PDF attachments&nbsp;that&nbsp;references&nbsp;a specific customer order number and&nbsp;associated purchased items which&nbsp;entices&nbsp;the recipient&nbsp;to&nbsp;go to the&nbsp;Ajour&nbsp;Lingerie&nbsp;website. If the user visits the website&nbsp;and&nbsp;navigates to the&nbsp;"Contact Us" page, they are then&nbsp;given the option to enter&nbsp;the order number in the&nbsp;order ID. If entered,&nbsp;the contact page then&nbsp;redirects the user&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;landing page&nbsp;that&nbsp;links to&nbsp;and explains how to&nbsp;open the Excel sheet.&nbsp;The&nbsp;Excel sheet contains macros that, if enabled&nbsp;by the user, will download&nbsp;BazaLoader.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{7e8b84b9-8e35-413c-bf23-fd06962f92eb}{208}" paraid="532095926"><img alt="Shape" src="data:image/png;base64," unselectable="on"><img alt="Shape" src="data:image/png;base64," unselectable="on"><img src="data:image/png;base64," unselectable="on">&nbsp;<em>Figure&nbsp;3:&nbsp;Email&nbsp;Lure&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{7e8b84b9-8e35-413c-bf23-fd06962f92eb}{233}" paraid="1064647585"><img src="data:image/png;base64," unselectable="on">&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{7e8b84b9-8e35-413c-bf23-fd06962f92eb}{238}" paraid="899670413"><em>Figure&nbsp;4:&nbsp;Ajour&nbsp;Lingerie&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{7e8b84b9-8e35-413c-bf23-fd06962f92eb}{254}" paraid="1595406429"><img src="data:image/png;base64," unselectable="on"><em>Figure&nbsp;5:&nbsp;Landing Page&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{5df120f9-3767-4e67-996f-35d753e560cb}{22}" paraid="1530670168"><img src="data:image/png;base64," unselectable="on"><em>Figure&nbsp;6:&nbsp;Enable Content to deliver&nbsp;BazaLoader&nbsp;</em></p>

<h3 paraeid="{5df120f9-3767-4e67-996f-35d753e560cb}{41}" paraid="892147405">Flowers&nbsp;at Rose World&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3>

<p paraeid="{5df120f9-3767-4e67-996f-35d753e560cb}{65}" paraid="2125535705">This campaign is nearly identicalenticing users to check an order number. The&nbsp;campaign delivered&nbsp;PDF attachments with references to&nbsp;purchases at&nbsp;the&nbsp;Rose World&nbsp;website. If the user visits the&nbsp;website, navigates to&nbsp;"Contact Us",&nbsp;and enters&nbsp;the order number in the&nbsp;order ID, the site will redirect the user to a landing page. This landing page links to and explains how to open the Excel sheet. The Excel sheet contains macros that, if enabled, will download&nbsp;BazaLoader.&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{5df120f9-3767-4e67-996f-35d753e560cb}{105}" paraid="645388603"><img src="data:image/png;base64," unselectable="on">&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{5df120f9-3767-4e67-996f-35d753e560cb}{108}" paraid="818502182"><em>Figure&nbsp;7:&nbsp;Rose World Customer Order&nbsp;Email&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{5df120f9-3767-4e67-996f-35d753e560cb}{118}" paraid="227014935"><img src="data:image/png;base64," unselectable="on">&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{9964a995-4da5-4c5a-849f-35fa80b45d1a}{96}" paraid="1671594654"><em>Figure&nbsp;8:&nbsp;Invoice with website&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{5df120f9-3767-4e67-996f-35d753e560cb}{211}" paraid="969491556"><img src="data:image/png;base64," unselectable="on">&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{5df120f9-3767-4e67-996f-35d753e560cb}{214}" paraid="890305685"><em>Figure&nbsp;9:&nbsp;Rose World&nbsp;contact page&nbsp;and enter your order number&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{5df120f9-3767-4e67-996f-35d753e560cb}{230}" paraid="1845022135"><img src="data:image/png;base64," unselectable="on"><em>Figure&nbsp;10: Enable Macros to receive&nbsp;Bazaloader&nbsp;</em></p>

<h3 paraeid="{5df120f9-3767-4e67-996f-35d753e560cb}{239}" paraid="764916446">Conclusion:&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3>

<p paraeid="{5df120f9-3767-4e67-996f-35d753e560cb}{239}" paraid="764916446">Proofpoint researchers have observed a steady growth in actors using&nbsp;BazaLoader&nbsp;as a 1st&nbsp;stage downloader. In addition to the uptick in&nbsp;BazaLoader&nbsp;distribution, there is active development of&nbsp;BazaLoader,&nbsp;particularly&nbsp;during the month of October 2020.&nbsp; These recent&nbsp;BazaLoader&nbsp;campaigns&nbsp;exemplify affiliate actors leveraging a loader that is&nbsp;increasingly&nbsp;popular&nbsp;and more reliant&nbsp;on&nbsp;human interaction.&nbsp;Further, the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.proofpoint.com/us/corporate-blog/post/cybersecurity-101-what-social-engineering">social engineering</a> features rely on the timeliness of&nbsp;the&nbsp;Valentines Day&nbsp;holiday&nbsp;and the intrinsic user curiosity to see what they may have ordered. From a technical point of view, we have provided a number of IOCs and ET signatures below as this <a href="https://www.proofpoint.com/us/threat-reference/malware">malware</a> family is used to execute on any number of actor or affiliate&nbsp;intentions, actions, and&nbsp;objectives.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{af5c23d3-da25-44a3-b968-99656902eaa6}{116}" paraid="1657624320"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>

<p paraeid="{af5c23d3-da25-44a3-b968-99656902eaa6}{116}" paraid="1657624320"><strong>IOCs&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p>

<table border="1" data-tablelook="1184" data-tablestyle="MsoTableGrid">
	<tbody>
		<tr role="row">
			<td data-celllook="4369" role="rowheader">
			<p paraeid="{af5c23d3-da25-44a3-b968-99656902eaa6}{130}" paraid="1956498364"><strong>IOC&nbsp;</strong></p>
			</td>
			<td data-celllook="4369" role="columnheader">
			<p paraeid="{af5c23d3-da25-44a3-b968-99656902eaa6}{137}" paraid="120257770"><strong>IOC Type&nbsp;</strong></p>
			</td>
			<td data-celllook="4369" role="columnheader">
			<p paraeid="{af5c23d3-da25-44a3-b968-99656902eaa6}{144}" paraid="598930292"><strong>Description&nbsp;</strong></p>
			</td>
			<td data-celllook="4369" role="columnheader">

			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr role="row">

			</td>

			</td>
			<td data-celllook="4369">

			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr role="row">
			<td data-celllook="4369" role="rowheader">
			<p paraeid="{af5c23d3-da25-44a3-b968-99656902eaa6}{198}" paraid="1652198210">447b4c867b7147afe178d73adf8113fc33f6399f03707e4308efa36e0859bf86&nbsp;</p>
			</td>
			<td data-celllook="4369">
			<p paraeid="{af5c23d3-da25-44a3-b968-99656902eaa6}{205}" paraid="2111875395">SHA256&nbsp;</p>
			</td>
			<td data-celllook="4369">
			<p paraeid="{af5c23d3-da25-44a3-b968-99656902eaa6}{212}" paraid="1968673152">BazaLoader&nbsp;Hash&nbsp;</p>
